msgid "Machine-readable output"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:294
#: f21b20cd57be48fcbde21f12708bfe61
msgid ""
"The commands ``qvm-template list`` and ``qvm-template info`` provide "
"machine-readable output in both pipe(``|``)-separated and JSON format. "
"See the ``qvm-template`` man page for details."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:297
#: 8633ba091bcb4d8aa5055ccfdd00d617
msgid "Interactions with existing tools"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:301
#: ce6e2eda6c8846b89a7673822f88c01a
msgid "``qvm-remove``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:304
#: 1e23a161fd4c44938d16addea9ff67ae
msgid ""
"The existing ``qvm-remove`` tool should behave identically to ``qvm-"
"template remove`` – albeit without fancy features like disassociation. "
"This is unlike the previous situation where ``qvm-remove`` cannot remove "
"RPM-installed templates."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:306
#: 5ecc958dfc624f94ad1e94abc701ed27
msgid ""
"Notably, the metadata needs no special handling as it is stored in VM "
"features and thus automatically consistent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:309
#: 4624001ccc8640e2b9405cbed57d827f
msgid "Renaming and cloning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../developer/system/template-manager.rst:312
#: 8e94af4bb2184396acefb489cd7b7d31
msgid ""
"A template is treated as non-manager-installed once renamed or cloned. "
"However, relevant metadata in the VM features is still retained for "
"future extension and to serve as a hint for the user."
msgstr ""

